p: Stratford virus (STRV) RNA was detected in an isolate of Anopheles annulipes collected in Australia from 1995–2013 [ 54]. Sequence analysis based on part of the NS5 gene sequence displayed 95–99% homology among the different isolates of STRV, and 2% divergence was detected between the isolates collected in 1995–2013 and the first isolates of 1961. The main vector of STRV is thought to be Aedes spp., without important contribution by Culex spp. [ 54].
